<task id="R3-051" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit + migrate `notification-new-emails.json`</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>Audit found one A1-class defect: the original FetchXML had NO user-membership filter at all (only `directioncode=0` + `createdon>=X` + inner-join to `sprk_matter`), so it would have returned inbound emails on EVERY matter in the tenant â€” not just the executing user's matters â€” directly contradicting the playbook description. No `sprk_matterteammember` reference (so not the literal A1 broken-join pattern), but the same root cause (no working membership scoping). Migrated using the same pattern as task 050: added `Lookup My Matters` LookupUserMembership node (actionType=52, entityType=sprk_matter, roles=[owner,assignedAttorney,assignedParalegal], outputVariable=myMatters) between Start and Query New Emails; added `<condition attribute='regardingobjectid' operator='in' value='{{joinIds myMatters.ids}}'/>` to the email filter; preserved the `sprk_matter` link-entity (added `alias='matter'`) so the body template's `regardingMatterName` keeps working. Edges updated (Startâ†’Lookup My Mattersâ†’Query New Emails). Positions shifted +100x to make room. JSON re-validated.</completion-notes>
    <phase>P6</phase>
    <parallel-group>L (with 050, 052)</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <estimated-effort>1h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>playbook-config,migration,audit</tags>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-emails.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <dependencies>041, 042</dependencies>
  </metadata>
